{"questionId":"22646887","questionHtml":"<p>Write down the null and alternative hypotheses for this test.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi>L</mi></msub><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi>D</mi></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi>L</mi></msub><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&gt;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi>D</mi></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>:</mo></math>&nbsp;The (population) mean height of Latvian women is equal to the (population) mean height of Dutch women&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo></math>&nbsp;The (population) mean height of Latvian women is greater than the (population) mean height of Dutch women&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award at most <em><strong>A0A1</strong></em> if the hypotheses explicitly refer to the “sample” and not the population. For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&gt;</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msub></math> award <em><strong>A0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22646887","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.4f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the null and alternative hypotheses for this test.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}